  "informal_statement": "For every real x ≥ 2, ∑_{p≤x} log p / p = θ(x)/x + ∫_{(2,x]} θ(t)/t² dt.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Abel summation with f(t) = 1/t over the prime-log weights: the boundary term is θ(x)/x and the derivative of 1/t produces the θ(t)/t² integral kernel.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem theta_abel_prime_log_identity :\n    ∀ x : ℝ, 2 ≤ x →\n      ∑ p ∈ Finset.Icc 1 ⌊x⌋₊ with p.Prime, Real.log p / (p:ℝ)\n        = Chebyshev.theta x / x +\n          ∫ t in Set.Ioc (2:ℝ) x, Chebyshev.theta t / t^2",
